Class FilterBase

  • java.lang.Object
    • cutthecrap.utils.striterators.FilterBase
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IFilter, IPropertySet, Serializable, Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Advancer, Appender, BackchainTypeResourceIterator.PushbackFilter, Contractor, Expander, Filter, LookaheadTupleFilter, Mapper, Merger, NOPFilter, PrefixFilter, Resolver, SolutionSetStatsFilter, Sorter, TupleFilter, TupleRemover, TupleTransformer, Visitor

    public abstract class FilterBase
extends Object
implements IFilter, Cloneable
    Used with Filterator by Striterator to filter returned objects. This can represent either a single IFilter or a chain of IFilters.

      • filter

        public final Iterator filter(Iterator src,
              Object context)
        Description copied from interface: IFilter

        The filter method is provided to allow the creation of the filtering iterator.

        Any implementation should follow the following pattern:

          public Iterator filter(Iterator src, Object context) {
                return new Filterator(src, context, this);
        }
        This pattern makes the source iterator, the evaluation context, and the IPropertySet annotations visible to the runtime striterator implementation.
        Specified by:
        filter in interface IFilter
